        "type": "text",
        "content": "Is it possible to set the TrustZone boundaries runtime?"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "In general for most RA MCUs, that are using a Cortex-M33 core the TrustZone boundaries cannot be changed in the firmware. And the MCUs need to be placed in either SCI or USB boot mode. However for the new E-devices like RA4E2 and RA6E2 the Trustzone boundaries can be set runtime by writing to the following registers:"
